{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:21:46.084461+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:PagCvE | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 66328420ac4a69b088f99ae399388044682c17f2)", "id": "lc_e5a0ed2f-da14-45d2-9927-c792f69efab0"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:PagCvE | # Book sources\n| MCP:PagCvE | \n| MCP:PagCvE | The app fetches public-domain books from the sources listed below. None of\n| MCP:PagCvE | them require a user-bound API key; the only authentication some endpoints\n| MCP:PagCvE | accept is a server-side rate-limit token shipped via CI secrets.\n| MCP:PagCvE | \n| MCP:PagCvE | | Source | Endpoint | Auth | Notes |\n| MCP:PagCvE | |--------|----------|------|-------|\n| MCP:PagCvE | | Feedbooks (public) | `https://catalog.feedbooks.com/catalog/public_domain.atom` | none | OPDS catalog |\n| MCP:PagCvE | | Project Gutenberg mirror | `https://www.gutenberg.org/ebooks/...` | none | HTML scraping |\n| MCP:PagCvE | | Internet Archive Bookreader | `https://archive.org/details/...` | none | OAuth optional for higher rate limits |\n| MCP:PagCvE | | Standard Ebooks | `https://standardebooks.org/feeds/atom/all` | none | Atom feed |\n| MCP:PagCvE | \n| MCP:PagCvE | If you add a new source, append a row above and update the test fixture in\n| MCP:PagCvE | `test/services/source_fixtures_test.dart`.", "id": "lc_73cbe07e-780f-4e49-b4bb-ad479b5ea25e"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "4e15468e-6f25-4e30-b8ab-d4622c1e0bad", "tool_call_id": "call_f2189eed365b41b79240a968", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:22:03.981369+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on the README and `docs/sources.md`, the app fetches public‑domain books from four external sources. None of them require a user‑bound API key; some accept optional OAuth for higher rate limits. Here’s the summary:\n\n| Source | Authentication | Notes |\n|--------|----------------|-------|\n| **Feedbooks (public)** | Anonymous (none) | OPDS catalog endpoint |\n| **Project Gutenberg mirror** | Anonymous (none) | HTML scraping |\n| **Internet Archive Bookreader** | Optional OAuth token (for higher rate limits) | OAuth can be used but is not required |\n| **Standard Ebooks** | Anonymous (none) | Atom feed |\n\n**Key points:**\n- No source requires a mandatory API key.\n- All sources can be accessed anonymously.\n- The Internet Archive endpoint accepts an optional OAuth token to increase request limits.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 573, "prompt_tokens": 6472, "total_tokens": 7045, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 396, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 6016}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "112011dfd6134d7393a93a4a6ecb0c16", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead67-9065-7aa1-93ca-77f078cff6ce-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 6472, "output_tokens": 573, "total_tokens": 7045, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 6016}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 396}}}}]}}}
